pace agency, sent manned missions to the Moon in the 1960's and 70's. Most recent space projects have focused on smaller, lighter machinery, such as ' in 2004, which reached space after being carried part of the way by a instead of launching from the ground. As of last week, the most powerful rocket in use was the Delta IV, operated by the . It costs about US$435 million per launch, while SpaceX says the Falcon Heavy will cost US$90 million per launch.\nNASA is also working on a heavy-duty rocket, the Space Launch System, but there have been delays."}
