ank robberies, to gain entry. The detained suspect's identity is restricted to 'Stefan W' owing to Polish privacy legislation.\nAdamowicz was taken to the , where Dr. Tomasz Stefaniak was met with applause early today upon announcing to journalists Adamowicz remained alive. \"The next hours will decide everything,\" Stefaniak said. Politicians and the Archbishop of Gda\u0144sk, , were reported by local media to have visited the hospital while Adamowicz received emergency surgery.\nAdamowicz subsequently was announced to have died. Health Minister said \"We couldn\u2019t win,\" and the city flag is at half-mast. Gda\u0144sk residents donated blood by the hundreds today in a bid to assist. Vigils nationwide this evening were attended by thousands.\nAdamowicz, 53, has supported LGBT rights and and the inclusion of minority groups. He recently condemned after vandalism against a synagogue in the city. Adamowicz was at the event after collecting money for the organisation in Gda\u0144sk's streets alongside volunteers nationwide.\nA potential charge of murder against Stefan W carries a possible life sentence. Prosecutor Krzysztof Sierak told reporters today psychiatric assessments will be carried out to confirm if Stefan W is fit for trial."}
